thread.title: Copper Buoyed by U.S.-China Progress

author: David Hodari
title: Copper Buoyed by U.S.-China Progress
text:
Copper prices extended a recent rally Tuesday, rising to the highest point in almost a month.
May-dated futures rose 1.1% to $3.119 a pound, settling at the highest value since April 25. The market moved within a tight range throughout May before jumping higher Tuesday morning.
